The ideal candidate is social and can convey their personality through email. If you are cordial, well-written, and organized, we&#39;ll get along just fine. Solid networking skills and a basic knowledge of online advertising or website ownership are a huge help.</p>
<p>
This is a full-time job with benefits.</p>
<p>
<strong>In This Job You Will:</strong></p>
<p>
Find and recruit the best sites on the web and help them get hooked up to our network through any means necessary (aka mostly email)<br />
Work as part of a growing team that has full control over the entire publisher process at BSA<br />
Help us continually improve every aspect of the publisher-facing side of the company, with help from an awesome group of in-house designers and developers that can turn your ideas into reality within minutes (ok, days...)<br />
Eventually attend recruiting meetings with specific publishers, or attend conventions as recruitment efforts ramp up</p>
<p>
<strong>The ideal candidate:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Is familiar with the basics of online advertising, either as an advertiser, or a publisher</li>
<li>
Can write a damn good email</li>
<li>
Is friendly and legitimately likes getting to know people better</li>
<li>
Wants to work at a fast growing, bootstrapped, and profitable company</li>
<li>
Enjoys working within a small group of highly talented folks vs. being a cog in a giant machine</li>
<li>
Is a self-starter, doer; we don&rsquo;t micro-manage</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>The Benefits:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work closely with a core group of folks within an agile and lean company</li>
<li>
